NEW DELHI, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Data released by the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers (SIAM) Friday said domestic passenger vehicle (PV) sales grew by 11 percent year-on-year in February to 291,928 units. A year ago the sales figure was 262,984 units. Two-wheeler sales in India continued to grow at a moderate pace of about 8 percent in February to 1,129,661 units. Three-wheeler sales were 50,382 units in February 2023, the data further showed. The apex body representing all major vehicle and vehicular engine manufacturers said the total production of passenger vehicles -- three-wheelers, two wheelers and quadricycles in February was 1,754,922 units. It further said the total production of passenger vehicles from April 2022 to February 2023 was 22,750,797 units. "PV posted its highest-ever sales of February and the three-wheeler segment posted appreciable growth this month, compared to last two years. The two-wheeler segment posted a moderate growth of 8 percent in February 2023, compared to February 2022," said Rajesh Menon, director general of SIAM.  â– 